===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|Breton|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|Britto|lang=la}} or its Celtic equivalent (compare Welsh {{term|Brython|lang=cy}}).<!--''From Anglo-Saxon '''Bryton''' or '''Briton''', an inhabitant of Britain (or of Britany, which was sometimes used interchangeably with Britain). All these originate from the Ancient British *'''Brittānos''' (pl.'''Brittānī''').  The short form '''Brit''' (or '''Bryt''') apparently was used during the Saxon era.''-->

